dc_description_s: This layer is a georeferenced raster image of the historic paper map entitled: Middelsexiae cum Hertfordiae comitatu = Midlesex & Hertford Shire. It was published after Joannem Janssonium in 1646. Scale [ca. 1:160,000]. Quatuor milliaria Anglica conficiunt unum milliare Germanicum = 7 cm. The image inside the map neatline is georeferenced to the surface of the earth and fit to the 'British National Grid' coordinate system. All map collar and inset information is also available as part of the raster image, including any inset maps, profiles, statistical tables, directories, text, illustrations, index maps, legends, or other information associated with the principal map. This map shows features such as drainage, cities and other human settlements, territorial boundaries, shoreline features, and more. Relief, woodlands, and city views shown pictorially. Includes also decorated cartouche, coat of arms of England in upper left and lower right corner; Bar scale illustrated with a scene from counryside. This layer is part of a selection of digitally scanned and georeferenced historic maps from the Harvard Map Collection. These maps typically portray both natural and manmade features. The selection represents a range of originators, ground condition dates, scales, and map purposes.
